HEADWORD: Whimling
<hw>Whim"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Whim</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <def>One given to whims; hence, a weak,
childish person; a child.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go, <qex>whimling</qex>, and fetch two or three grating
loaves.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whimmy</ent>⟦br⟧
